en the open and closed positions thereof and a second position wherein the bight of the ushaped arm engages and maintains the clapper disk in the sealingly closed position thereof a selectively rotatable control arm operatively coupled with the ushaped arm and utilized to move the ushaped arm between the first and second positions thereof type application filed october   publication date april   inventors yoram ringer stephen j meyer thomas edwin archibald preaction sprinkler valve assemblies related dry sprinkler devices and fire protection sprinkler systems publication number  abstract a thermal trigger assembly for remote mechanical actuation of another fire protection system component includes an activation component having a base and a movable member a bias member biases the movable member from a preactivation to an activated position with respect to the base a thermally responsive element retains the movable member in the preactivation position until a predetermined thermodynamic condition is reached when the thermally responsive element loses structural integrity a flexible connector includes a flexible hollow outer cable housing with one end configured to be stationarily preferably fixedly connected with the base a flexible cable is inside the outer cable housing for sliding movement therein and has one end configured to be stationarily preferably fixedly connected with the movable member the flexible cable is moved with respect to the outer cable housing by movement of the movable member upon loss of structural integrity by the thermally responsive element type application filed july   publication date february   inventors stephen j meyer yoram ringer thomas edwin archibald firesprinkler protection system and method for a combustible concealed space publication number  abstract a firesprinkler protection system for a combustible concealed space having a sloped ceiling has a plurality of firesprinklers including pendent sprinklers and sidewall sprinklers disposed beneath the sloped ceiling each pendent sprinkler provides a spray pattern that is generally circular cylindrical about the sprinkler each sidewall sprinkler provides a spray pattern that is generally rectangular in shape the hydraulic demand for each sprinkler is substantially equivalent to the projection hydraulic demand for the horizontal footprint projection of the sloped ceiling on the floor a piping system is coupled to each sprinkler by a plurality of branch lines is sized to provide the hydraulic demand for each sprinkler type application filed june   publication date december   applicant globe fire sprinkler corporation inventor stephen j meyer ordinary hazard extended coverage sidewall sprinklers and systems patent number  abstract an extended coverage sidewall automatic fire sprinkler includes a generally tubular body with a central passageway and a central axis one end of the passageway forms an outlet at one end of the tubular body a closure at the one end of the tubular body at least essentially generally closes the passageway a trigger positioned to releasably retain the closure at the outlet closes the passageway a deflector at a discharge end of the sprinkler is coupled with the tubular body facing and spaced axially away from the outlet and intersects the central axis the tubular body has a k factor greater than  type grant filed november   date of patent april   assignee tyco fire products lp inventors stephen j meyer george s polan james e golinveaux low pressure early suppression fast response sprinklers patent number  abstract a low pressure early suppression fast response sprinkler includes a generally tubular body having an inlet ends an opposing discharge end and an internal passageway extending between the inlet and discharge ends with a k factor greater than  where the k factor equals the flow of water in gallons per minute through the internal passageway divided by the square root of the pressure of water fed into the tubular body i